<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1682,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Diagnosis. Worker (
<figureCitation box="[386,498,1682,1708]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Figs. 
<number box="[451,498,1682,1708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
</figureCitation>
; Tab. I). Head width 
<quantity box="[746,920,1682,1708]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="8.6" metricValueMin="8.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="0.86" valueMin="0.84">0,84–0,86 mm</quantity>
; pubescence of clypeus and lower parocular area simple, relatively dense and long; in discal area of clypeus, piligerous points separated by distance shorter than hair length, some long branched hairs on juxtaclypeal area (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1070,1762,1788]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[1056,1070,1762,1788]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); malar space short, 
<date box="[1317,1346,1762,1788]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<number box="[1317,1328,1762,1788]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
x
</date>
diameter of fl. 
<number box="[246,260,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,343,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[329,343,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); clypeus short, about 
<number box="[610,621,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[632,647,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
of its maximum width and 
<number box="[968,979,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[990,1005,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="5.0">5</number>
of clypeocellar distance; integument of upper gena with fine tessellation; posterior margin of tibia III sinuous, posterior parapenicillum markedly sinuous, S-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[378,450,1882,1908]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[433,450,1882,1908]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); keirotrichiate area on inner surface of tibia III with a glabrous area medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1682,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[274,356,1922,1948]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Figs. 
<number box="[340,356,1922,1948]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="6.8" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.6">3</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[369,432,1922,1948]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,219,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,182,1263]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., male, Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 6, sternum VI; 7, sternum VII; 8, sternum VIII; 9, genitalia, dorsal view; 10, genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185348/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">6–10</figureCitation>
; Tab. I). SVI with broad hairy medial area deeply concave (
<figureCitation box="[1130,1201,1922,1948]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,219,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,182,1263]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., male, Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 6, sternum VI; 7, sternum VII; 8, sternum VIII; 9, genitalia, dorsal view; 10, genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185348/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[1184,1201,1922,1948]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); median projection of 
<collectionCode box="[184,241,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">SVII</collectionCode>
slender and Y-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[521,594,1962,1988]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,219,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,182,1263]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., male, Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 6, sternum VI; 7, sternum VII; 8, sternum VIII; 9, genitalia, dorsal view; 10, genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185348/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[577,594,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
); genitalia with gonocoxite wider than long, recurved on distal margin and projecting laterally on the gonostylus articulation (
<figureCitation box="[793,922,2002,2028]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,219,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,182,1263]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., male, Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 6, sternum VI; 7, sternum VII; 8, sternum VIII; 9, genitalia, dorsal view; 10, genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185348/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Figs. 
<number box="[859,922,2002,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="9.1">9, 10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" box="[198,506,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<typeStatus box="[198,310,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Holotype</typeStatus>
, worker (Tab. I).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Dimensions. Total length, 1.98 mm; forewing length, from apex of costal sclerite to wing tip, 1.88 mm (including tegula, 2.10 mm); maximum head width, 0.84 mm; abdomen width (
<collectionCode box="[1081,1133,232,258]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">TIII</collectionCode>
), 0.76 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" box="[198,993,271,298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Integument color. Typical of the genus (genus diagnosis, items 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[939,952,271,297]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">c</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[967,983,271,297]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">d</emphasis>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Vestiture. Clypeus and lower parocular area up to upper margin of antennal alveolus with dense semiappressed, relatively long (0.04 mm) simple hairs (in discal area of clypeus, distance between piligerous points about half as long as hair length), not shining; some long branched hairs on juxtaclypeal area (
<figureCitation box="[1348,1417,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1403,1417,392,418]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); above antennal alveolus, dense but shorter, finer and erect; on frons, sparser, erect and longer (0.06 mm); on vertex, between lateral ocelli, denser and longer than on frons. On mesoscutum, few hairs, very sparse and erect, on discal area ca. 0.04 mm long, longer (0.07 mm) and slightly curved on anterior corners; on lateral borders of scutellum some long (0.14 mm) erect hairs. On propodeum, in addition to plumose pubescence around propodeal spiracles, short simple hairs, semi-appressed, from spiracle to posterior border next to base of coxa III; some longer sparse hairs on vertical surface of propodeum. Tergum II practically glabrous, only some microscopic hairs on anterior concave surface and some long hairs on anterior corners; 
<collectionCode box="[1264,1311,672,698]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">TIII</collectionCode>
–TVI with some hairs on sides and anterior margin, very short on 
<collectionCode box="[817,864,712,738]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">TIII</collectionCode>
and progressively longer to TVI; on 
<collectionCode box="[1316,1375,712,738]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">TVII</collectionCode>
long erect hairs scattered on surface. Lateral margins of tibia III with pale-whitish translucent hairs, 0.22 mm long; on postero-distal corner, the posterior parapenicillum composed of a tuft of plumose hairs and 
<number box="[1266,1310,792,818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
setae very long, simple and strongly sinuous to the apex (as in 
<figureCitation box="[760,831,832,858]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[814,831,832,858]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Integument sculpture. Typical of the genus (item 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[790,806,871,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">b</emphasis>
), except for the upper third of gena, behind the eye, with very fine tessellation. The concave region of anterior vertical surface of TII marked with a fine and relatively dense punctuation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Form and proportions (measurements in Table I). Head slightly wider than long. Eye 2.4x longer than wide; upper interorbital distance as long as eye length; inner orbits convergent below (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1253,1317,1032,1058]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1306,1317,1032,1058]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus very short, about 
<number box="[367,378,1072,1098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[389,404,1072,1098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
of its maximum width and 
<number box="[751,762,1072,1098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[773,788,1072,1098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="5.0">5</number>
of clypeocellar distance; inner corners separate from orbits by 1.4x malar space length; malar space as long as the diameter of fl. 
<number box="[1045,1059,1112,1138]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
(as in 
<figureCitation box="[1140,1208,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1194,1208,1112,1138]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Interalveolar distance 
<date box="[220,249,1152,1178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[220,231,1152,1178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
x
</date>
alveolus diameter. Interocellar distance little longer than 
<date box="[923,952,1152,1178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[923,937,1152,1178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
median ocellus diameter and ocellorbital distance ca. 1.6x. Supraclypeal area swollen between alveoli, gently sloping down to median sulcus; frons medially depressed-sulcate. Antennal scape as long as 4.8x its diameter, and 0.6x alveolocellar distance; flagellum + pedicel as long as 
<date box="[484,513,1272,1298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[484,498,1272,1298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
scape length. Mandible length 
<number box="[886,896,1272,1298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<date box="[906,938,1272,1298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[906,922,1272,1298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
clypeocellar distance. Tibia III triangular, 2.6x longer than wide; posterior border sinuous and postero-distal angle projecting, acute (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1275,1347,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1329,1347,1312,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" box="[198,1171,1352,1378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Male (specimen 
<number box="[393,484,1352,1378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="910053.0">910053</number>
, from the same nest of the 
<typeStatus box="[800,906,1352,1378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
; 
<figureCitation box="[918,999,1352,1378]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 
<number box="[983,999,1352,1378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="6.8" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.6">3</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1013,1075,1352,1378]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,219,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,182,1263]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., male, Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 6, sternum VI; 7, sternum VII; 8, sternum VIII; 9, genitalia, dorsal view; 10, genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185348/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">6–10</figureCitation>
; Tab. I).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Dimensions. Total length, 2.22 mm; forewing length, from apex of costal sclerite to wing tip, 1.82 mm (including tegula, 2.06 mm); maximum head width, 0.82 mm; abdomen width (
<collectionCode box="[1081,1133,1432,1458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">TIII</collectionCode>
), 0.64 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Integument color, vestiture, integument sculpture. As in worker, only some areas of face slightly rugose: between ocelli and just above the alveoli. Pilosity of inner margin of mandible and sides of TVI and 
<collectionCode box="[1377,1436,1512,1538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">TVII</collectionCode>
much longer than in worker. The hairs of pre-genital sterna and gonostylus as in 
<figureCitation box="[1095,1222,1552,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,219,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,182,1263]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., male, Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 6, sternum VI; 7, sternum VII; 8, sternum VIII; 9, genitalia, dorsal view; 10, genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185348/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 
<number box="[1160,1222,1552,1578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Form and proportions (measurements in Table I). Head slightly wider than long. Eye 
<date box="[1195,1225,1592,1618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[1195,1209,1592,1618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than wide, strongly convergent below (as in 
<figureCitation box="[549,621,1632,1658]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[605,621,1632,1658]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); upper interorbital distance 0.8x eye length. Clypeus longer than in worker, 0.53x longer than wide and 
<number box="[594,604,1672,1698]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<date box="[614,646,1672,1698]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[614,630,1672,1698]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="4.0">4</number>
x
</date>
clypeocellar distance; malar space practically null (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1347,1420,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,197,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,197,1876]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 1, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 2, tibia III, worker; 3, head, male. Leurotrigona pusilla Moure &amp; Camargo, paratype, Manaus, AM, Brazil: 4, head and detail of the clypeus vestiture, worker; 5, tibia III, worker. Scales = 0.02 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185347/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1404,1420,1672,1698]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Interalveolar distance a little shorter than median ocellus diameter, slightly longer than alveolorbital distance and about 
<number box="[278,288,1752,1778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<date box="[299,331,1752,1778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[299,314,1752,1778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="5.0">5</number>
x
</date>
alveolocellar distance. Interocellar distance ca. 
<date box="[909,939,1752,1778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[909,923,1752,1778]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
median ocellus diameter and ocellorbital distance less than 
<date box="[368,405,1792,1818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<number box="[368,380,1792,1818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
x.
</date>
Upper half of frons as in worker, but lower portion, just above antennal alveoli, more strongly depressed medially, with a convex surface flanking the depressed area. Scape shorter, 3.8x longer than its diameter and a little shorter than half the alveolocellar distance. Flagellum + pedicel 0.86 mm long, ca. 3.7x longer than scape. Mandible toothless, a little shorter than half the clypeocellar distance. Tibia III and basitarsus III swollen. Pre-genital sterna and genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[849,976,1952,1978]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,219,1243]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,182,1263]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Leurotrigona crispula sp. nov., male, Puerto Triunfo, Antioquia, Colombia: 6, sternum VI; 7, sternum VII; 8, sternum VIII; 9, genitalia, dorsal view; 10, genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185348/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 
<number box="[914,976,1952,1978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
